  "text": "The new Combo lure technology represents an improvement over previously available monitoring systems; however several nonresolved issues should be addressed with future research. Trap densities, action thresholds, and the relevance of female capture data are important issues to investigate, as well as the interaction among plant volatiles and pheromones [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, female distribution, distance of flight, and other field behavior have been very difficult to measure due to the lack of effective attractants [CITATION_2] ), but pear ester may facilitate these types of studies ).",
